What is the clique number of the following graph?

V = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}

E = {(1,2), (1,3), (2,3), (3,4), (3,5), (4,5)}

Hint: A clique is a subset of vertices in a graph where each vertex is adjacent to all other vertices in the subset. The clique number is the size of the largest clique in the graph.
